# Copy to .env.local and adjust if needed. Nothing here is secret — Occulta reads Sepolia
# through a public RPC by default and needs no API key or private key to run.

# Optional: point reads at your own Sepolia RPC instead of the public fallback
# (https://ethereum-sepolia-rpc.publicnode.com). Must be exposed to the client, so never put
# a key-bearing provider URL here for a public deployment.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SEPOLIA_RPC_URL=https://ethereum-sepolia-rpc.publicnode.com

# Optional: which settled epoch the reveal card and netting section decrypt/display. Defaults to
# 0, the documented demo epoch (buy 20 + buy 15 - sell 5 = net 30 USDC, BUY) the rest of the page
# is built around. Only change this if re-homing the demo to a different settled epoch.
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURED_EPOCH=0
